{"article_id":"UOOivabs8CDmRvst","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Senate voted Friday to end debate on Judge Brett Kavanaugh ' s Supreme Court nomination ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"setting the stage for a final vote in the chamber Saturday evening","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"-- where the White House now believes","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"it has the votes","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"to confirm Kavanaugh .","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"The vote","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"to invoke cloture","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"was 51-49 .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"While the vote was not necessarily indicative of the final confirmation vote ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"it moved him one step closer to sitting on the highest court in the land ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"with three out of four key undecided senators voting `` yes ''","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"to advance the nomination .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"Republican Sens . Susan Collins , R-Maine , Jeff Flake , R-Ariz. , and West Virginia Democratic Sen. Joe Manchin , voted to move forward .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Sen. Lisa Murkowski , R-Alaska , voted `` no . ''","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"With a 51-49 majority , Republicans ca n't afford more than one defection","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"if all Democrats were to vote together .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Collins is expected to announce her decision in a speech on the Senate floor at 3 p.m. Friday .","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"Flake later said","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"he intends to vote `` yes , '' `` unless something big changes . ''","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"The math for Republicans became somewhat trickier late Thursday","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"when Sen. Steve Daines , R-Mont. , said","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"he would be attending his daughter 's wedding in Montana on Saturday .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"he would return to cast the decisive vote","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"if needed .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"President Trump welcomed the vote in a tweet ,","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"he was `` very proud '' of the Senate .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"A source familiar with the lobbying efforts","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"to confirm Kavanaugh","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"told Fox News","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that the White House believes","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"it has the votes","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"to confirm Kavanaugh .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"The source said","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"that the White House believes","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Murkowski will ultimately be a `` no , ''","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"but Manchin , Collins and Flake will all vote `` yes . ''","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Kavanaugh ' s nomination was embroiled in a controversy","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"that gripped the nation","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"after multiple women made sexual assault allegations","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"originating from his time in high school and college .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"The most prominent allegation was from California professor Christine Blasey Ford ,","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"who said","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"that Kavanaugh assaulted her at a high school party .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"That allegation resulted in a high-stakes Senate Judiciary hearing last week","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"where both Ford and Kavanaugh testified .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"Democrats said","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"the allegations were credible","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"and deserved a full investigation ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"while Republicans accused Democrats of using uncorroborated allegations","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"to scuttle or delay the nomination","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"-- leading to a stream of angry flashpoints between lawmakers .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"The accusations eventually led to President Trump","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"ordering an FBI investigation .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"Republicans","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"who had seen the FBI ' s report","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"the FBI had produced no credible corroboration of the allegations .","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"JUDICIARY COMMITTEE RELEASES EXECUTIVE SUMMARY OF SUPPLEMENTAL FBI REPORT ON KAVANAUGH","depth":2},{"id":60,"text":"Protesters flooded the capital in the days ahead of the vote ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"and clashed with Republican lawmakers in an effort","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"to sway their votes ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"and initially appeared to have some success .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Flake demanded the limited FBI investigation last week","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"after being cornered in an elevator by screaming protesters moments before a Senate Judiciary Committee vote","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"to recommend Kavanaugh ' s nomination .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Other Republicans later pushed back against protesters .","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"Sen. Orrin Hatch , R-Utah , told","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"protesters","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"chasing him","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"to \" grow up \"","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"while Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , responded to one protester ' s call","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"for Kavanaugh to take a polygraph test ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"asking :","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"\" Maybe we can dunk him in water","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"and see","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"if he floats ? \"","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"After the vote on Thursday , protesters once again yelled at Republican senators","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"as they walked through the Senate building .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"Ahead of the cloture vote , Senate Judiciary Chairman Chuck Grassley , R-Iowa , urged the Senate to say \" no to mob rule. \"","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"He also blasted Democrats for their treatment of Kavanaugh ,","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"describing it as \" nothing short of monstrous . \"","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"\" The conduct of left-wing dark money groups and allies in this body have shamed us all , \"","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"\" The fix was in from the very beginning . \"","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , said","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"that the vote was `` a pivotal day for us here in the Senate . ''","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"`` The ideals of justice","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that have served our nation for so long","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"are on display , ''","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"he said ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"calling the last two weeks a `` disgraceful spectacle . ''","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"But Democrats had pointed to not only the sexual assault allegations ,","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"which they described \"","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"but also questions about Kavanaugh ' s temperament during the hearing last week","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and whether he had lied about his drinking during high school and college , and what certain references in his high school yearbook meant .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"They also sought to paint him as a justice","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"that would swing the court deeply to the right .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer , D-NY , accused him of being evasive in his answers during his confirmation hearings on key topics .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"his views are \" deeply at odds with the progress","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"America has made in the last century of jurisprudence","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"and at odds with what most Americans believe . \"","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Sen. Dianne Feinstein , D-Calif. , on the Senate floor before the vote , raised concerns","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"that Kavanaugh would vote to overturn Roe v Wade","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"-- the 1973 decision","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"that found a constitutional right to abortion --","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"and was extreme on gun rights .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"But she said","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"the last few weeks had raised further concerns , particularly his emotional defense in front of the Senate Judiciary Committee ,","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"where he had blasted Democrats for their treatment of the sexual assault allegations against him .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"\" This behavior revealed a hostility and belligerence","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"unbecoming of someone","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"seeking to be elevated to the Supreme Court , \"","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Kavanaugh defended his behavior in an op-ed for The Wall Street Journal late Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"in which he expressed some regret for his fiery attack on Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"\" I was very emotional last Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"more so","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"than I have ever been .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"I might have been too emotional at times , \"","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"\" I know","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"that my tone was sharp ,","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"and I said a few things","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"I should not have said . \"","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"He added :","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"`` I hope","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"everyone can understand","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"that I was there as a son , husband and dad .","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"I testified with five people foremost in my mind :","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"my mom , my dad , my wife , and most of all my daughters . ''","depth":13}],"relations":[{"